{"lemma":"أَلْيَة","slug":"أَلْيَة","root":"#.ل.#","root_slug":"_-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ل-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1134","n1148","n1149"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mechanism","examples":[{"text":"آلِيَّةُ عَمَل","english":"mechanism of action"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"machinery, automation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"automaticity"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Relative noun (nisba) composed of آلة (ʔāla) + ـِيَّة (-iyya)."},"ipa":["/ʔaː.lij.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1134","headword_ar":"اَلِيَّةٌ","root":"Alw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A falling short;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a falling short of what is requisite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one ought to do;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flagging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remissness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slowness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tardiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaA","text_ar":"اَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaS~ara","text_ar":"قَصَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliy~apF","text_ar":"اَلِيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) Hence the prov., (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA HaDiy~apF falaA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا حَضِيَّةً فَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliy~apF","text_ar":"اَلِيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If I be not in favour, and high estimation, I will not cease seeking, and labouring, and wearying myself, to become so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if thou fail of good fortune in that which thou seekest, fall not short,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flag not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be not remiss, in showing love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection, to men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"may-be thou wilt attain somewhat of that which thou wishest: originally relating to a woman who becomes displeasing to her husband: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HZw","text_ar":"حظو"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is one of the proverbs of women: one says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if I be not in favour, and high estimation, with my husband, I will not fall short,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be remiss, in that which may render me so, by betaking myself to that which he loveth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HZw","text_ar":"حظو"},{"kind":"text","text":":) Meyd says that the two nouns are in the accus. case because the implied meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA A^akuno HaZiy~apF falaA A^akuno A^aliy~apF","text_ar":"اـِلَّا اَكُنْ حَظِيَّةً فَلَا اَكُنْ اَلِيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter noun being [accord. to him] for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=liyapN","text_ar":"ا=لِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which it may be put for the sake of conformity [with the former]; and the former having the signification of the pass. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoZaY","text_ar":"اَحْظَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", or that of the part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiYa","text_ar":"حَظِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiyato","text_ar":"حَظِيَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 78.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oath;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliy~aA","text_ar":"اَلِيَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alowapN","text_ar":"اَلْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulowapF","text_ar":"اُلْوَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iliywapN","text_ar":"اـِلِيوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAlAuluw~apu muval~avapF","text_ar":"والاُلُوَّةُ مُثَلَّثَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAliA^alowapu mvl~vpF","text_ar":"والِاَلْوَةُ مثلّثةً"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) it is [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliywapN","text_ar":"اَلِيوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylapN","text_ar":"فَعِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaAyaA","text_ar":"اَلَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh.) A poet says, (namely, Kutheiyir, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qaliyluA AlA^alaAyaA HaAfiZN liyamiynihi\n                      \n                     \n                        waA_ino sabaqato minohu AlA^aliy~apu bar~ati"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A person of few oaths, who keeps his oath from being uttered on ordinary"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean occasions; but if the oath has proceeded from him at any former time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hastily, it proves true"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) or, as IKh relates it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliylu AlA_ilaA='i","text_ar":"قَلِيلُ الاـِلَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning, he says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliylu AlA_ylaA='i","text_ar":"قَلِيلُ الاـيلَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being suppressed: see 4. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","T","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1148","headword_ar":"اَلْيَةٌ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buttock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buttocks, rump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"posteriors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajiyzapN","text_ar":"عَجِيزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or [more properly]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajuzN","text_ar":"عَجُزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) of a man &c., (M,) or of a sheep or goat, (Lth, T, S,) and of a man, (Lth, T,) or of a ewe: (ISk, T:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh and fat thereon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) you should not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloyapN","text_ar":"اـِلْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, K,) a form mentioned by the expositors of the Fs, but said to be vulgar and low; (TA;) nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liy~apN","text_ar":"لِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, K,) with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the S, [but in a copy of the S, and in one of the T, written without teshdeed,] a form asserted to be correct by some, but it is rarer and lower than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloyapN","text_ar":"اـِلْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though it is the form commonly obtaining with the vulgar: (TA:) the dual. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyaAni","text_ar":"اَلْيَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T, S,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyataAni","text_ar":"اَلْيَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes occurs: (IB:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaS~u AlA^aloyatayoni","text_ar":"اَلَصُّ الاَلْيَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to the Zenjee, (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lS","text_ar":"لص"},{"kind":"text","text":",) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the buttocks cleaving together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in that art.:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyaAtN","text_ar":"اَلْيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaAyaA","text_ar":"اَلَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) the latter anomalous. (M.) Lh mentions the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw A^aloyaAtK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو اَلْيَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he has"},{"kind":"text","text":"large"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buttocks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_aloyapN","text_ar":"اـَلْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to every part of what is thus called. (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst.: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of fat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat of the tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunobahN","text_ar":"دُنْبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a sheep. (KL.) [Both of these significations (the “tail,” and “fat of the tail,” of a sheep) are now commonly given to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liy~ap","text_ar":"لِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", a corruption of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapN","text_ar":"اَلْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned above: and in the K, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TunobuwrN","text_ar":"طُنْبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said that the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunobaho bar~aho","text_ar":"دُنْبَهْ بَرَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu AlHamali","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الحَمَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu Als~aAqi","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ السَّاقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The muscle of the shank;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaApu Als~aAqi","text_ar":"حَمَاةُ السَّاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmw","text_ar":"حمو"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AAF, M, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu AlA_ibohaAmi","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الاـِبْهَامِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The portion of flesh that is at the root of the thumb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is also called its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the part to which corresponds the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu Alkaf~i","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the portion of flesh in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) the little finger to the prominent extremity of the ulna next that finger, at the wrist: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the portion of flesh in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thumb."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu AlxanoSiri","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الخَنْصِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The portion of flesh that is beneath the little finger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is described above, as called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from that finger to the prominent extremity of the ulna, at the wrist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu Alyadi","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ اليَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, T.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyataA Alkaf~i","text_ar":"اَلْيَتَا الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyap","text_ar":"اَلْيَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thumb"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"described above as also called by itself"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu Alkaf~i","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~ap","text_ar":"ضَرَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the little finger"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respecting which see the next preceding sentence]. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqadami A^aloyapu","text_ar":"القَدَمِ اَلْيَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part of the human foot upon which one treads, which is the portion of flesh beneath"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the little toe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapu AlHaAfiri","text_ar":"اَلْيَةُ الحَافِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hinder part of the solid hoof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M.)"}],"source_refs":["K","M","Lth","T","S","ISk","TA","AZ","IB"]},{"entry_id":"n1149","headword_ar":"اـِلْيَةٌ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyapN","text_ar":"اَلْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}